{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"44ec479e-b3ad-4861-81ff-889ebe791957","content":"You can use `dotnet watch test` with the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\nThis will:\n- **`dotnet watch test`** — re-run tests automatically on file save (hot reload).\n- **`--filter \"FullyQualifiedName~...\"`** — only run tests whose name contains that string. The `~` operator means \"contains\".\n\nYou can also filter by just the method name:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"Name=ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\nNow every time you save a file, only that single test will re-run.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e8126bce-62f7-4aea-8779-6e4668f1a474","outputTokens":177,"requestId":"BD05:C42E6:1D10ACE:209FB25:6A07C24E"},"id":"e2821307-5e27-40b4-af4b-399b444db7f4","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:03:15.798Z","parentId":"f04cc2e1-108d-4e88-9191-ca7a5b9ddde1"}
